## How many people to test with

You should think about the number of people to test with, compared to the number of people who will use the service. 

Research suggests <a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/summary-quant-sample-sizes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener norferrer">40 participants is an adequate number for most quantitative methods (opens in a new tab)</a>. 

You may be able to <a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/why-you-only-need-to-test-with-5-users/" target="_blank" rel="noopener norferrer">test with fewer people for qualitative research methods (opens in a new tab)</a>.

You should also consider how many people may have access needs when thinking of the number of people to recruit as participants.

